                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11358: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-02-04T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >February 4, 1931—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 4—1:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>12. The following telegram has been sent to the Legation: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“February 14, 3 p.m. U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Oahu</hi> fired upon
                            yesterday by field piece at mileage 117. Fire silenced with twenty-two
                            3-inch shells and <pb facs="1048" n="938" xml:id="pg_938"/> 1750 rounds
                            machine gun. No casualties on <hi rend="italic">Oahu</hi>. Steam launch
                                <hi rend="italic">Mei Lu</hi>, squadron’s [<hi rend="italic"
                                >Standard Oil Company?</hi>] vessel, fired upon at mileage 204 and
                            at Temple Hill yesterday. No casualties.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Department.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
